column5: This dude has to be a relative of MisFish's
I actually own something like that in pretty mint shape  My father in law bought one new in about 55--used it twice---now I have it wrapped in plastic.
Thats great AND you can pay in installments. Oh how the times have changed.
2 models with FULL REVERSE!! WHOO HOO!! 	Great find TJ.
What is partial reverse? Is that where you have to take the motor off the bracket and point it backwards?
having one of those mint, is prolly worth more than a new current model.

Don't know how much they are worth now.....BUT for my money I'll take a newer models since I remember them B A S T A R D S....LOL......spent more time trying to get them started and keep them running then fishing....LOL....those were the days I want to forget....
Nothing quite like an EVERUDE  All the same, neat find.
